    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change color of mui radio button in react js, you can use  in  component. it will change color of mui radio button in‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change color of mui radio button in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">color=\"secondary\"</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;radio></code> component. it will change color of mui radio button in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How to change color of mui radio button in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui radio in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI radio.</li>\n<li>Use the radio Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI radio.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Radio <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Radio\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the Radio Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">Radio</code> component in your react js. For example, Radio buttons let users make a mutually exclusive choice. Only one selection is allowed from the available set of options. You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Radio/></code> component make a radio in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Radio\n  color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"secondary\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Change this to the desired color</span>\n  checked<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>selectedOption <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'option2'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  onChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleRadioChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"option2\"</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        </code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material change color of mui radio button example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">Radio</code> Component. you can use <code class=\"language-text\">color=\"secondary\"</code> in radio and to change color of mui radio button in react js. </p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Radio <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material/Radio'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> FormControlLabel <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material/FormControlLabel'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">MyComponent</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>selectedOption<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> setSelectedOption<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'option1'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleRadioChange</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setSelectedOption</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>event<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>target<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>value<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>FormControlLabel\n        value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"option1\"</span>\n        control<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Radio\n            color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"primary\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Change this to the desired color</span>\n            checked<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>selectedOption <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'option1'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            onChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleRadioChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"option1\"</span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        label<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Option 1\"</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>FormControlLabel\n        value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"option2\"</span>\n        control<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Radio\n            color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"secondary\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Change this to the desired color</span>\n            checked<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>selectedOption <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'option2'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            onChange<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleRadioChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            value<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"option2\"</span>\n          <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        label<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Option 2\"</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Add more FormControlLabel components as needed */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> MyComponent<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and change color of mui radio button in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 249px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f3f3a0e98f83a97c96d792347531aec5/1fa9f/color-radio-button.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.56962025316456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRmYAAABXRUJQVlA4IFoAAAAwBACdASoUAAkAPtFWpUwoJKOiMAgBABoJQApggf8zgIn/GBTRHF+eRMAA/nk7iGpQXtOw7gTrcdmd4P0U8nb8bmu54ywn+JsdYQ30PXOoS0NfQBQeBXZXsAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, color, radio, button\"\n        title=\"React, color, radio, button\"\n        src=\"/static/f3f3a0e98f83a97c96d792347531aec5/1fa9f/color-radio-button.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f3f3a0e98f83a97c96d792347531aec5/81b7c/color-radio-button.webp 158w,\n/static/f3f3a0e98f83a97c96d792347531aec5/1fa9f/color-radio-button.webp 249w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 249px) 100vw, 249px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program change color of mui radio button in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=distracted-field-cgshrp\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to change color of mui radio button in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"July 21, 2023","description":"Example of change color of mui radio button in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui radio button group in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-07-21-how-to-make-mui-radio-button-group-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui chip with tootip in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-07-20-how-to-make-mui-chip-with-tootip-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-07-22-how-to-change-color-of-mui-radio-button-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-07-21-how-to-make-mui-radio-button-group-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-07-20-how-to-make-mui-chip-with-tootip-in-react-js/"}},
